        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 11:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1115 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles south of Lake Meredith, or 20 miles north of Amarillo. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
